<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Webpage Example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #eef2f3;
            color: #333;
        }

        h1, h2 {
            color: #4caf50;
        }

        a {
            color: #4caf50;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        img {
            display: block;
            margin: 10px auto;
            max-width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border: 2px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: auto;
            background-color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        footer {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            color: #666;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Button Styling */
        button {
            background-color: #4caf50; /* Green background */
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049; /* Darker green on hover */
        }
    </style>
    <script>
        // JavaScript function to show an alert
        function showAlert() {
            alert("Button clicked! This is a simple alert.");
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to My Simple Webpage</h1>
        <p>This page demonstrates basic HTML elements such as headings, paragraphs, images, and links.</p>

        <h2>About This Page</h2>
        <p>Learning HTML is essential for web development. It allows you to structure your content and create visually appealing pages. With the addition of CSS, you can style your webpage to look great!</p>

        <h2>A Beautiful Image</h2>
        <p>Below is an example of an image with a caption:</p>
        <figure>
            <!-- Replace the src URL with your actual image -->
            <img src="https://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_trulli.jpg" alt="A beautiful building">
            <figcaption>Figure: Trulli houses in Alberobello, Italy</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <h2>Useful Resources</h2>
        <p>Here are some great resources to learn web development:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.w3schools.com" target="_blank">W3Schools</a> - A comprehensive resource for learning HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</li>
            <li><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org" target="_blank">MDN Web Docs</a> - Detailed documentation for web technologies.</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org" target="_blank">freeCodeCamp</a> - Interactive lessons and projects for beginners.</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Button to trigger the alert -->
       
        <button onclick="showAlert()">Click Me!</button>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>© 2024 Simple Webpage. Designed with ❤️ by a budding web developer.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
